Onboarding & Core Flow — Mid-fidelity Sketches

Overview
- Purpose: Mid-fi designs for onboarding (signup → profile → initial tasks) and core post-onboarding dashboard.
- Deliverable: mid-fi wireframes, component specs, user flow, design decisions.
- File: output/design/onboarding_sketches.pdf (this document)

Target Platform
- Primary: Web (responsive). Please confirm mobile native priority (ask: #ai-mobile).

User Flow (linear)
1. Welcome / Value props + CTA (Sign up / Log in)
2. Signup options (Email, Google SSO, SSO button if enabled)
3. Email signup flow (email -> verify -> set password)
4. Profile setup (name, preferences — optional skip)
5. Initial tasks / quick tour (3-step checklist to surface value)
6. Dashboard (core flow)

Screens (mid-fi)
- Screen A: Welcome
  [ Top: logo | Help ]
  [ Big headline: "Get started in minutes" ]
  [ Two CTAs: Sign up (primary), Log in (link) ]
  [ Small: "Or continue with" — Google SSO button ]

- Screen B: Email Signup
  [ Card ]
  [ Email field ]
  [ Password field ]
  [ Re-type password (optional, can be replaced by show-password + strength) ]
  [ Primary CTA: Create account ]
  [ Link: Use SSO instead ]

- Screen C: Email Verify (enter code) / Magic link fallback
  [ Code input (6 boxes) ]
  [ Resend link / use magic link ]

- Screen D: Profile Setup
  [ Avatar placeholder ] [ Name ] [ Role (dropdown) ] [ Preferences toggles ]
  [ Skip for now ] [ Continue ]

- Screen E: First-run Checklist / Initial Tasks
  [ 3 cards horizontally with progressive completion ]
  [ Primary: Start guided task ]
  [ Secondary: Skip tour ]

- Screen F: Dashboard (post-onboarding)
  [ Left nav ] [ Main content: tasks / summary ]
  [ Top-right: profile menu ]

Component Specs
- Card layout: 16px border radius, 24px padding
- Grid: single column center card max-width 680px on desktop, 16px gutters
- Buttons: Primary (blue 16px padding), Secondary (ghost)
- Inputs: 44px height, 12px radius, label above field
- Progress indicator: step dots + textual step "Step 2 of 4"

Accessibility & microcopy
- Use clear error states under inputs (red 14px) + success toasts
- Offer skip options for low-friction onboarding
- Provide SSO explanation tooltip: "Use your Google account — no password created"

Key Design Decisions (rationale)
- Single-column centered card: reduces cognitive load and works well responsively.
- Progressive disclosure for profile info: ask minimal info first to increase completion.
- Optional tour: lets experienced users skip while ensuring new users see value.

Open Questions / Blockers (need answers to finalize)
- Auth approach: JWT vs sessions vs SSO — #ai-backend please confirm. This impacts microcopy ("Continue with Google" vs session messaging) and error flows.
- Primary target breakpoints: responsive web only or mobile-first? #ai-mobile please confirm if native is priority.
- Any brand color / typography tokens? If not, I used system defaults (will provide style tokens in hi-fi).

Acceptance criteria for frontend mocks
- All onboarding states represented: empty, loading, success, error, retry.
- SSO & email flows mocked (if SSO enabled, show SSO button + tooltip).
- Profile skip path available.

Next steps
- Once #ai-backend confirms auth and provides example API responses, I will produce hi-fi screens + exported assets (SVGs) within 24h.
- Handoff to #ai-frontend: implement mid-fi. #ai-qa: prepare acceptance tests based on above criteria.

Files attached
